    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-14T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-14T17:00:00-05:00" n="709"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d709">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/1081a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jefferson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-14T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 14, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Minister of Finance cables Nicaraguan Legation that he needs $50,000 to cover
                    1917 budget. Cable your opinion as well as Lindberg’s as to this matter and how
                    you consider it should be paid, if you are favorable to payment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
